  "description": "A California Court Ruled that Uber and Lyft Drivers are Independent Contractors On August 10, 2020, a California judge ruled that Uber and Lyft are to classify their drivers as employees when this entire time they were being classified as independent contractors.&nbsp; The State of California brought a lawsuit against Uber and Lyft claiming that they were misclassifying their workers.&nbsp; Uber and Lyft have since appealed the decision, which could bring years of litigation defending their business models."
